article.description: — Frankie Policelli scored 22 points as Charleston (SC) beat Drexel 80-70 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Policelli scores 22, Charleston (SC) defeats Drexel 80-70
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- — Frankie Policelli scored 22 points as Charleston (SC) beat Drexel 80-70 on Saturday night. Policelli added five rebounds for the Cougars (18-7, 9-3 Coastal Athletic Association). Ante Brzovic added 19 points while going 8 of 14 from the floor, including 1 for 4 from 3-point range, and 2 for 3 from the line, and also had five rebounds. CJ Fulton had 13 points and was 5 of 8 shooting (3 for 4 from 3-point range). The Dragons (15-10, 8-4) were led in scoring by Amari Williams, who finished with 20 points and eight rebounds. Drexel also got 12 points and seven rebounds from Luke House. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
